<div class="plugin-faq">
    <h3>Frequently Asked Questions</h3> 
    <ol class="plain">
        <li>
            <div>Why would I want to see things like HTTP_COOKIE, I can see my cookies in FireBug?</div>
            Its important to remember that the data that you see in FireBug (or other such tools) in only 
            a client perspective of the data that was sent. In some cases what the server actual receives  
            can be very different. In some cases, proxies can adjust such values making some issues very 
            difficult to diagnose. Glimpse shows these values to make these cases much easier to debug.
        </li> 
    </ol>
</div>